english:
  title: Royal Edict Conferring the Title of Foreknowing National Master upon Master Doseong of Okryongsa Temple
  author: Choe Eung-cheong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    By Royal Edict:

    The Celestial Emperor's favor shines anew, and thus He grants a dwelling place. Where the aura of royalty dwells, there must first appear a sign. How then could an exceptional man not perceive what is yet to come?

    Master Doseong of Okryongsa Temple emerged in response to this age, bearing a compassionate heart that aids those who align with Heaven's will. He illuminated the ancient way of the Buddha and the patriarchs, championing the dharma. He grasped and upheld the imperial enterprise, fulfilling what the wise had foreseen. He opened the path of the Sacred Age and pioneered vast territories, creating the foundation of royal virtue. Such profound merit shall never be forgotten.

    The Luminous Sovereign honored him as a Meditation Master, and the Solemn Ancestor bestowed upon him the title of Royal Master. His name endures imperishable, inscribed anew upon stone monuments, and we honor him with the utmost reverence, respectfully observing the statutes of former kings. Thus we prepare ceremonial gifts and bestow upon him the formal rites of ennoblement.

    Listen well, all ministers in attendance: understand fully my deepest intention. This day we grant you, Master Doseong, the certificate of title as Foreknowing National Master of Okryongsa Temple. Receive it with dignity.

    Therefore this edict is issued. Let it be known and obeyed. This decree is sent; words cannot express all that should be said.
  footnotes:
    - Doseong (道詵, 827-898) was a legendary Korean Buddhist monk credited with geomantic wisdom and influence on Korean political history, revered across dynastic periods.
    - The titles 'Luminous Sovereign' (顯廟) and 'Solemn Ancestor' (肅祖) refer to Korean royal ancestors who posthumously honored Doseong.
    - '''Foreknowing National Master'' (先覺國師) reflects the traditional belief that Doseong possessed prophetic insight into Korea''s destiny.'
